Step-by-Step Procedure (Creating VLAN)
1️⃣ Create the Network Topology

Open GNS3 and add the devices.

Add:

1 Switch

4 PCs

Connect them like this:

        PC1
         |
        SW
       /  \
    PC2   PC3
            \
             PC4

VLAN grouping:

PC	VLAN
PC1	VLAN 100
PC2	VLAN 100
PC3	VLAN 200
PC4	VLAN 200
2️⃣ Assign IP Address to PCs

Configure IP addresses:

PC	IP Address
PC1	10.1.1.1
PC2	10.1.1.2
PC3	10.1.1.3
PC4	10.1.1.4

Example command inside PC:

PC1> ip 10.1.1.1 255.255.255.0
PC2> ip 10.1.1.2 255.255.255.0
PC3> ip 10.1.1.3 255.255.255.0
PC4> ip 10.1.1.4 255.255.255.0
3️⃣ Access the Switch CLI

Open switch console and type:

Switch> enable
Switch# configure terminal
4️⃣ Create VLANs

Create VLAN 100 and VLAN 200

Switch(config)# vlan 100
Switch(config-vlan)# name Lab1
Switch(config-vlan)# exit

Switch(config)# vlan 200
Switch(config-vlan)# name Lab2
Switch(config-vlan)# exit
5️⃣ Assign Ports to VLANs

Assume connections:

Port	PC	VLAN
Fa1/1	PC1	VLAN100
Fa1/2	PC2	VLAN100
Fa1/3	PC3	VLAN200
Fa1/4	PC4	VLAN200

Configure ports.

PC1 Port
Switch(config)# interface fa1/1
Switch(config-if)# switchport mode access
Switch(config-if)# switchport access vlan 100
Switch(config-if)# no shutdown
Switch(config-if)# exit
PC2 Port
Switch(config)# interface fa1/2
Switch(config-if)# switchport mode access
Switch(config-if)# switchport access vlan 100
Switch(config-if)# no shutdown
Switch(config-if)# exit
PC3 Port
Switch(config)# interface fa1/3
Switch(config-if)# switchport mode access
Switch(config-if)# switchport access vlan 200
Switch(config-if)# no shutdown
Switch(config-if)# exit
PC4 Port
Switch(config)# interface fa1/4
Switch(config-if)# switchport mode access
Switch(config-if)# switchport access vlan 200
Switch(config-if)# no shutdown
Switch(config-if)# exit
6️⃣ Verify VLAN Configuration

Run:

Switch# show vlan

Expected output:

VLAN   NAME   STATUS   PORTS
100    Lab1   active   Fa1/1 Fa1/2
200    Lab2   active   Fa1/3 Fa1/4
7️⃣ Test Connectivity
From PC1
PC1> ping 10.1.1.2

✔ Connection established (same VLAN)

PC1> ping 10.1.1.3

❌ Host unreachable (different VLAN)

From PC4
PC4> ping 10.1.1.3

✔ Connection established

PC4> ping 10.1.1.1

❌ Host unreachable

8️⃣ Final Result

✔ PC1 ↔ PC2 communicate (VLAN100)
✔ PC3 ↔ PC4 communicate (VLAN200)
❌ VLAN100 cannot communicate with VLAN200
